This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new method for training generative adversarial networks (GANs) and ensembles using the discrepancy measure. The paper also presents explicit generalization guarantees for the proposed method, which is a common topic in machine learning research. 

The paper also involves computer vision (cs.CV) as it uses benchmark datasets to evaluate the proposed method. Additionally, the paper involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it proposes a new method for generating data. 

The paper may also belong to the sub-categories of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SD (Software Engineering) as it involves the development of efficient algorithms for training GANs and ensembles.
